snippet: The Obama administration said 7.3 million of those who enrolled had paid their premiums and still had coverage, the vast majority paying less than $100 a month.
abstract: Obama administration says 7.3 million people who bought private health insurance under Affordable Care Act paid their premiums and are still enrolled; says vast majority are paying less than $100 a month.
lead_paragraph: The Obama administration said 7.3 million of those who enrolled had paid their premiums and still had coverage, the vast majority paying less than $100 a month.
